<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F49FEC748A755A5FE2BFB4D" pageId="263" pageNumber="264" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418F49FEC748A755A5FB10FB69" blockId="263.[151,1438,649,1358]" pageId="263" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F49FEC748A755A5FE0EFD51" bold="true" box="[151,427,649,674]" pageId="263" pageNumber="264">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48F49FEC74A8455A5FCAAFD51" box="[692,783,649,673]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.9" pageId="263" pageNumber="264" unit="mm" value="6.9">6.9 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible brown and clypeus yellow with central region black; antenna testaceous, except segment 1 ventrally black; mesosoma black, except lateral margins of pronotum weakly reddish; metasoma black, except posterior half testaceous; legs brown, except coxae and trochanters partly whitish, proximal half of metacoxa black, tarsi testaceous. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 12:6:37:17:14:10:9:8:7:11. Head (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F49FEC74B9E5435FBBFFCC1" box="[942,1050,793,817]" captionStart="PLATE 75" captionStartId="260.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[200,1397,222,1838]" captionTargetId="figure-138@260.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="260" captionText="PLATE 75. A, F, H. Heads. B, E, G, I. Chelae. C. Antennal segments 3–6. D, J. Male genitalia. A, B. Dryinus bellicus, female (A) and holotype (B) (from Olmi 1987a). C–E. D. browni, female (C), male from Sri Lanka (D) and female from Laos (E) (from Olmi 1984). F, G. D. bruneianus, holotype (from Olmi 1987c). H–J. D. cavifrons, vertex (H), holotype (I) and paratype (J) (from Olmi 1986). Scale bar 0.32 mm for B and I, 0.26 mm for D, 0.36 mm for E, 0.59 mm for G and 0.24 mm for J." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278640" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278640/files/figure.png" pageId="263" pageNumber="264">Plate 75F</figureCitation>
) dull, reticulate rugose, with face narrow; frontal line complete; temple absent; occipital carina complete, laterally not reaching eyes, but running very near them; occiput excavated (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F49FEC74A00544DFD39FC89" box="[560,668,865,889]" captionStart="PLATE 75" captionStartId="260.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[200,1397,222,1838]" captionTargetId="figure-138@260.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="260" captionText="PLATE 75. A, F, H. Heads. B, E, G, I. Chelae. C. Antennal segments 3–6. D, J. Male genitalia. A, B. Dryinus bellicus, female (A) and holotype (B) (from Olmi 1987a). C–E. D. browni, female (C), male from Sri Lanka (D) and female from Laos (E) (from Olmi 1984). F, G. D. bruneianus, holotype (from Olmi 1987c). H–J. D. cavifrons, vertex (H), holotype (I) and paratype (J) (from Olmi 1986). Scale bar 0.32 mm for B and I, 0.26 mm for D, 0.36 mm for E, 0.59 mm for G and 0.24 mm for J." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278640" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278640/files/figure.png" pageId="263" pageNumber="264">Plate 75F</figureCitation>
); POL = 2; OL = 2; OOL = 8; OPL = 1. Pronotum shiny, strongly sculptured by keels around disc and on lateral regions; pronotum crossed by weak anterior transverse impression and strong posterior transverse impression; posterior collar distinct; pronotal tubercle not reaching tegula. Scutum dull, reticulate rugose. Notauli almost complete, almost reaching posterior margin of scutum. Scutellum dull, granulated. Metanotum dull, hairy, rugose. Propodeum reticulate rugose, with two longitudinal keels on posterior surface. Fore wing with two dark transverse bands; distal part of stigmal vein longer than proximal part (20:13). Hindwing hyaline, slightly darkened. Protarsal segments in following proportions: 23:5:9:20:33. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F49FEC748905371FEB4FB85" box="[160,273,1117,1141]" captionStart="PLATE 75" captionStartId="260.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[200,1397,222,1838]" captionTargetId="figure-138@260.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="260" captionText="PLATE 75. A, F, H. Heads. B, E, G, I. Chelae. C. Antennal segments 3–6. D, J. Male genitalia. A, B. Dryinus bellicus, female (A) and holotype (B) (from Olmi 1987a). C–E. D. browni, female (C), male from Sri Lanka (D) and female from Laos (E) (from Olmi 1984). F, G. D. bruneianus, holotype (from Olmi 1987c). H–J. D. cavifrons, vertex (H), holotype (I) and paratype (J) (from Olmi 1986). Scale bar 0.32 mm for B and I, 0.26 mm for D, 0.36 mm for E, 0.59 mm for G and 0.24 mm for J." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278640" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278640/files/figure.png" pageId="263" pageNumber="264">Plate 75G</figureCitation>
) with one strong subapical tooth and one row of 12 lamellae. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F49FEC74CD95371FAFDFB85" box="[1257,1368,1117,1141]" captionStart="PLATE 75" captionStartId="260.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[200,1397,222,1838]" captionTargetId="figure-138@260.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="260" captionText="PLATE 75. A, F, H. Heads. B, E, G, I. Chelae. C. Antennal segments 3–6. D, J. Male genitalia. A, B. Dryinus bellicus, female (A) and holotype (B) (from Olmi 1987a). C–E. D. browni, female (C), male from Sri Lanka (D) and female from Laos (E) (from Olmi 1984). F, G. D. bruneianus, holotype (from Olmi 1987c). H–J. D. cavifrons, vertex (H), holotype (I) and paratype (J) (from Olmi 1986). Scale bar 0.32 mm for B and I, 0.26 mm for D, 0.36 mm for E, 0.59 mm for G and 0.24 mm for J." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278640" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278640/files/figure.png" pageId="263" pageNumber="264">Plate 75G</figureCitation>
) with two rows of approximately 24 lamellae; distal apex with about 12 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F49FEC748F75389FE2BFB4D" blockId="263.[151,1438,649,1358]" box="[199,398,1189,1213]" pageId="263" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F49FEC748F75389FEAEFB4D" bold="true" box="[199,267,1189,1213]" pageId="263" pageNumber="264">Male.</emphasis>
